Year 2 envRS and PRS for longitudinal outcomes

Year 2 envRS were trained on parent-reported CBCL subscales for internalizing (intRS) and depression (depRS) symptoms. Here I am testing associations between year 2 envRS and longitudinal outcomes, plus the combination of envRS and MDD3 PRS.

PRS data based on MDD3 GWAS (from Poppy) were available for 4161 participants. At year 3, CBCL data were available for 8306 participants. A total of 2332 participants have year 3 CBCL data, PRS and year 2 envRS.

Model comparisons are run for:

m1 = cbcl ~ envRS
m2 = cbcl ~ envRS + PRS
m3 = cbcl ~ envRS*PRS

Lifetime MDD diagnosis (youth)

Depression diagnoses (lifetime and current) from youth-reported KSADS are available at year 2 (N=5730) and year 2 (N=5732).

Year 2 (cross-sectional)

For envRS-only analyses, there are 144 lifetime MDD cases, 27 current MDD cases and 278 cases with lifetime diagnoses of a depressive disorder (Major Depressive Disorder, Persistent Depressive Disorder (dysthymia), Depressive Disorder Unspecified).

Of those with both envRS and PRS at year 2 (N = 2440), there are 45 lifetime MDD cases, 10 current MDD cases and 92 cases with lifetime diagnoses of a depressive disorder (Major Depressive Disorder, Persistent Depressive Disorder (dysthymia), Depressive Disorder Unspecified).

Current analyses use just the lifetime MDD outcome.
